WEBVTT

00:00.024 --> 00:02.274
(Mary Jane voice-over)
<i>Previously on Being Mary Jane...</i>

00:02.532 --> 00:04.730
I am engaged,
and I want more.

00:04.740 --> 00:07.201
I like you, Sheldon,
and I like where this is going.

00:07.203 --> 00:08.645
(Kara)
You should have pushed harder.

00:08.647 --> 00:11.614
There is more to good journalism
than interrogating people, Kara.

00:11.616 --> 00:13.676
It's not journalism.
It's advocacy.

00:13.678 --> 00:15.468
Cynthia called
in sick tonight.

00:15.470 --> 00:17.368
<i>I get to do Prime Time tonight?</i>
- Yes!

00:17.370 --> 00:19.116
♪ It's probably a nip and tuck ♪

00:19.118 --> 00:20.889
I'm not attacking you,
Ms. Foy.

00:20.891 --> 00:23.648
I'm simply asking you
if you think that your book

00:23.658 --> 00:25.897
is being used to further
a political agenda.

00:25.907 --> 00:27.980
If you're really
paying attention to my show,

00:27.990 --> 00:30.272
you would see that we're not
all that different at all.

00:30.282 --> 00:34.105
When I look at you,
I see an ugly black woman too.

00:35.499 --> 00:38.364
[upbeat music]

00:38.374 --> 00:39.822
♪ ♪

00:39.832 --> 00:41.364
Welcome to the show,
Mary Jane Paul.

00:41.374 --> 00:42.948
I'm gonna start out by saying

00:42.958 --> 00:45.511
there is not one thing
that's ugly about you.

00:45.513 --> 00:47.322
Well, thank you,
and I kind of got myself

00:47.332 --> 00:49.655
in the hot seat on that one, huh?
- (Don) Yes, you did.

00:49.657 --> 00:52.489
But for the 12 people out there
who may still have dial-up

00:52.499 --> 00:54.572
and have no idea
what we're talking about,

00:54.582 --> 00:56.667
why don't we roll your interview
just from a couple days ago?

00:56.669 --> 00:58.332
And then we'll talk about it.

00:58.716 --> 01:00.706
If you were really
paying attention to my show,

01:00.716 --> 01:03.581
you would see that we're not
all that different at all.

01:03.591 --> 01:05.856
I mean, granted, we may not
agree on certain issues,

01:05.934 --> 01:07.622
but we're both fighting
to be heard

01:07.632 --> 01:10.664
and fighting to be taken
seriously and to be seen.

01:10.674 --> 01:12.752
So when it comes down to it,

01:12.916 --> 01:14.598
when I look at you,

01:15.740 --> 01:17.814
I see an ugly
black woman too.

01:19.674 --> 01:21.164
(Don)
Mary Jane Paul, come on.

01:21.174 --> 01:23.955
You know that you're not
supposed to become the story.

01:23.965 --> 01:26.164
We don't make the news;
we just report the news.

01:26.174 --> 01:29.330
How does it feel being on the other
side of that journalistic line?

01:29.340 --> 01:31.581
First of all, let me just say
that being an ugly black woman

01:31.591 --> 01:33.289
has absolutely nothing to do
with appearance.

01:33.299 --> 01:35.622
It's about the people
who feel that their voices

01:35.632 --> 01:38.039
have been stifled by society,

01:38.049 --> 01:40.913
people who are trying
to be heard,

01:40.923 --> 01:43.456
people who have had to
literally fight and scrape

01:43.466 --> 01:45.706
for every little thing that
they've been given in this life.

01:45.716 --> 01:47.205
Those people,

01:47.215 --> 01:50.122
those are the ugly black women
that I'm talking about.

01:50.132 --> 01:53.330
Regardless of race or gender
or sexual orientation,

01:53.340 --> 01:56.080
those people,
I am speaking for them,

01:56.090 --> 01:59.039
people who feel like
their stories don't matter.

01:59.049 --> 02:01.289
It's time for all of us
to stand up

02:01.299 --> 02:03.247
and demand that our voices
be heard.

02:03.257 --> 02:05.414
(Don) You are very passionate
about it, but you said "feel."

02:05.424 --> 02:07.664
Feelings aren't facts
when you're reporting the news.

02:07.674 --> 02:09.997
The fact is, there is a whole
segment of our population

02:10.007 --> 02:11.997
that feels that their stories
do not matter

02:12.007 --> 02:13.664
and that they have no voice.

02:13.674 --> 02:14.955
I'm speaking to those people.

02:14.965 --> 02:16.664
You're supposed to call that,
though,

02:16.674 --> 02:17.997
and then bring those stories
to life.

02:18.007 --> 02:20.664
But I want to ask you
about the Tea Party,

02:20.674 --> 02:22.122
the religious right.

02:22.132 --> 02:23.330
How do you respond to them

02:23.340 --> 02:25.080
calling you a racist
for calling this woman

02:25.090 --> 02:27.080
an ugly black woman
on national television?

02:27.090 --> 02:29.247
I think that the beautiful
thing about this country

02:29.257 --> 02:31.122
is that we are all entitled
to an opinion

02:31.132 --> 02:32.789
and to speak our opinions,

02:32.799 --> 02:35.372
and they are justifiably
doing that.

02:35.382 --> 02:37.789
I would also say
that there are several shows

02:37.799 --> 02:40.289
that preach
to their core values,

02:40.299 --> 02:42.289
and more power to them.

02:42.299 --> 02:44.372
I'm going to continue
to use my show,

02:44.382 --> 02:46.080
<i>Talk Back with Mary Jane Paul,</i>

02:46.090 --> 02:47.539
to speak to the people

02:47.549 --> 02:50.997
whose voices and stories
have been largely ignored

02:51.007 --> 02:54.664
and who deserve to have a seat
at the table,

02:54.674 --> 02:57.122
and I make no apologies
about that.

02:57.132 --> 03:00.122
[Living Colour's
<i>Cult of Personality]</i>

03:00.132 --> 03:03.913
♪ ♪

03:03.923 --> 03:06.205
(Corey Glover)
♪ Look in my eyes ♪

03:06.215 --> 03:09.913
♪ What do you see? ♪

03:09.923 --> 03:14.247
♪ The cult of personality ♪

03:14.257 --> 03:16.913
♪ I know your anger ♪

03:16.923 --> 03:20.164
♪ I know your dreams ♪

03:20.174 --> 03:22.581
♪ I've been everything
you want to be ♪

03:22.591 --> 03:24.164
(PJ) Hey, come on, Mary.

03:24.174 --> 03:25.539
You've been famous
for a while now,

03:25.549 --> 03:26.955
but even you got to admit

03:26.965 --> 03:28.664
all this buzz has gone
and made you a star.

03:28.674 --> 03:30.122
I don't pay attention
to that stuff.

03:30.132 --> 03:32.414
Girl, please; look,
you ain't even got to front,

03:32.424 --> 03:33.330
not for me, anyway.

03:33.340 --> 03:35.164
Whatever, PJ

03:35.174 --> 03:36.913
As quickly as it all comes,
it goes.

03:36.923 --> 03:38.039
It's just how I--

03:38.049 --> 03:39.664
(PJ) Not if mom can help it.

03:39.674 --> 03:42.497
Look, she been calling everybody
she knows bragging on you, okay,

03:42.507 --> 03:45.622
Telling the whole world how her
baby done hit the big time.

03:45.632 --> 03:48.122
(Mary Jane) I'm saying it's not
enough that I have my own news show

03:48.132 --> 03:49.955
or the fact that I was
on the air for, what,

03:49.965 --> 03:51.539
over a decade?

03:51.549 --> 03:53.539
<i>Yeah, Good Morning America</i>
starts talking about me,

03:53.549 --> 03:54.955
now--now that does it.

03:54.965 --> 03:57.164
(PJ) Don't trip. You
know how she is.

03:57.174 --> 03:58.664
But that new song is hot,
though.

03:58.674 --> 04:00.080
What new song?

04:00.090 --> 04:01.205
Hang on. You didn't hear it?

04:01.215 --> 04:02.913
No.

04:02.923 --> 04:04.706
Let me pull this up for you
right quick.

04:04.716 --> 04:06.913
(Corey Glover) ♪ Follow me ♪

04:09.466 --> 04:11.497
Listen to this.

04:11.507 --> 04:13.414
(woman)
♪ When I look at you ♪

04:13.424 --> 04:14.456
♪ I see an ugly black woman ♪

04:14.466 --> 04:16.329
[together] ♪ Oh ♪

04:16.339 --> 04:18.622
(PJ) Hey, look, you know you
made it when you get auto-tuned.

04:18.632 --> 04:21.329
Okay, not setting the bar
too high, are we?

04:21.339 --> 04:22.581
Jeez.

04:22.591 --> 04:24.289
(PJ) It's hot though, right?

04:24.299 --> 04:26.748
Yeah, it's cool.

04:26.758 --> 04:29.205
All right, hate to break up
the party, but I got to pull in.

04:29.215 --> 04:30.622
(PJ) All right, look,
do your thing.

04:30.632 --> 04:32.289
Bye, ugly black woman.

04:32.299 --> 04:33.913
All right, later, girl.

04:33.923 --> 04:36.622
Bye.
- Be careful what you say today.

04:36.632 --> 04:38.080
The whole world's watching.

04:38.090 --> 04:39.913
(Elizabeth) Great to meet
you, Mary Jane Paul.

04:39.923 --> 04:41.913
I'm actually a big fan
of your show.

04:41.923 --> 04:43.706
Oh? Oh?

04:43.716 --> 04:45.497
Critics argue
that your book tour

04:45.507 --> 04:48.205
is merely the blueprint for
the No Child Left Behind model

04:48.215 --> 04:50.789
that the Republicans used
during the Bush administration.

04:50.799 --> 04:52.539
You know what?
I'm not a politician.

04:52.549 --> 04:54.414
I'm a big fan of your show.

04:54.424 --> 04:56.913
Not at all. Not at all.
Not at all. Not at all.

04:59.299 --> 05:02.664
You know what? When I agreed
to appear on this program,

05:02.674 --> 05:04.748
I was going to be interviewed
by Cynthia,

05:04.758 --> 05:07.289
not by you
and your liberal agenda.

05:07.299 --> 05:08.372
I feel ambushed.

05:08.382 --> 05:09.664
I feel attacked.

05:09.674 --> 05:12.456
You have the opportunity to explain
your position right here...

05:12.466 --> 05:13.789
No.
- Right now.

05:13.799 --> 05:15.039
And I would love it
if you did that.

05:15.049 --> 05:16.581
You read my book?
Well, I've seen your show.

05:16.591 --> 05:18.122
And you're a race-baiter.

05:18.132 --> 05:21.122
You think the world sees you
as an ugly black woman,

05:21.132 --> 05:23.997
always the victim,
always misunderstood,

05:24.007 --> 05:25.748
and you're really
just a broken record.

05:25.758 --> 05:27.164
Oh. Oh.

05:27.174 --> 05:28.247
You're a woman.

05:28.257 --> 05:29.706
I'm a woman.

05:29.716 --> 05:31.247
I'm sorry.
I don't see the connection.

05:31.257 --> 05:32.748
(Mary Jane) Oh, let me
connect the dots for you.

05:32.758 --> 05:33.748
Excuse me?

05:33.758 --> 05:35.039
Let me connect the dots
for you.

05:35.049 --> 05:36.497
Excuse me?

05:36.507 --> 05:39.581
When I look at you,
I see an ugly black woman too.

05:39.591 --> 05:42.414
[Living Colour's
<i>Cult of Personality]</i>

05:42.424 --> 05:50.424
♪ ♪

05:55.923 --> 05:58.748
(Corey Glover)
♪ Look in my eyes ♪

05:58.758 --> 06:02.122
♪ What do you see? ♪

06:02.132 --> 06:06.497
♪ The cult of personality ♪

06:06.507 --> 06:09.205
♪ I know your anger ♪

06:09.215 --> 06:12.372
♪ I know your dreams ♪

06:12.382 --> 06:16.247
♪ I've been everything
you want to be ♪

06:16.257 --> 06:22.289
♪ Oh,
I'm the cult of personality ♪

06:22.299 --> 06:27.456
♪ Like Mussolini and Kennedy ♪

06:27.466 --> 06:30.664
♪ I'm the cult of personality ♪

06:30.674 --> 06:33.205
♪ The cult of personality ♪

06:33.215 --> 06:35.539
Oh, my God.

06:35.549 --> 06:40.247
[together] Mary Jane! Mary Jane!
Mary Jane! Mary Jane! Mary Jane!

06:40.257 --> 06:42.414
[laughs]

06:42.424 --> 06:44.039
(woman) Mary Jane!

06:44.049 --> 06:48.539
(Corey Glover)
♪ Neon lights, Nobel Prize ♪

06:48.549 --> 06:50.080
♪ When a mirror speaks ♪

06:50.090 --> 06:51.913
Hi.

06:51.923 --> 06:53.622
We love you, girl.

06:53.632 --> 06:55.122
Thank you so much for watching.

06:55.132 --> 06:59.664
(Corey Glover)
♪
♪You won't have to follow me ♪

06:59.674 --> 07:06.039
♪ Only you can set me free ♪

07:06.049 --> 07:08.789
Thank you so much for watching.

07:08.799 --> 07:10.414
I've got to get to work,
you guys.

07:10.424 --> 07:11.497
Thank you for watching.

07:11.507 --> 07:14.247
♪ ♪

07:14.257 --> 07:19.913
(Corey Glover) ♪ I sell the
things you need to be ♪

07:19.923 --> 07:23.997
♪ I'm the smiling face
on your TV ♪

07:24.007 --> 07:29.748
♪ Oh,
I'm the cult of personality ♪

07:29.758 --> 07:32.372
♪ I exploit you ♪

07:32.382 --> 07:35.748
♪ Still you love me ♪

07:35.758 --> 07:39.581
♪ I tell you one and one
makes three ♪

07:39.591 --> 07:43.748
♪ Oh,
I'm the cult of personality ♪

07:43.758 --> 07:46.164
♪ ♪

07:46.174 --> 07:48.122
Hey, Cynthia.

07:48.132 --> 07:49.955
Welcome back.
You feeling better?

07:49.965 --> 07:51.497
Let's just cut the crap, okay?

07:51.507 --> 07:54.164
You and I both know damn well
that I was never sick.

07:54.174 --> 07:55.706
(Mary Jane)
No, I didn't know that.

07:55.716 --> 07:58.247
Usually when people say things
like that, I tend to believe them.

07:58.257 --> 08:02.664
(Cynthia)
Yeah, well, it's all bullcrap.

08:02.674 --> 08:03.913
They're trying to push me out,

08:03.923 --> 08:06.330
and they are going to use you
to do it.

08:06.340 --> 08:08.748
When did they tell you that?
- They didn't.

08:08.758 --> 08:10.622
But when they tell you
you're looking tired

08:10.632 --> 08:12.581
and to go take a few days off
to relax,

08:12.591 --> 08:13.913
that's usually not a good sign.

08:13.923 --> 08:15.913
You're being paranoid.
- Am I?

08:15.923 --> 08:17.664
You're the face
of the network.

08:17.674 --> 08:19.539
They built this whole place
around you, Cynthia.

08:19.549 --> 08:21.539
If you had not helped them
launch it,

08:21.549 --> 08:22.997
there would be no SNC.

08:23.007 --> 08:25.205
All true, every word of it.

08:25.215 --> 08:27.205
But after what happened
to you at CNN,

08:27.215 --> 08:28.664
you should know better
than anyone

08:28.674 --> 08:30.622
that there is no loyalty
in news.

08:30.632 --> 08:33.121
This is different.
- Is it?

08:33.131 --> 08:35.205
Before this,
I spent 18 years at ABC,

08:35.215 --> 08:36.913
18 years,

08:36.923 --> 08:38.748
and they pushed me out the door
with little more fanfare

08:38.758 --> 08:39.955
than a sad-looking cake

08:39.965 --> 08:41.913
and a couple of cheap bottles
of champagne.

08:41.923 --> 08:43.955
You're, what, mid-40s?

08:43.965 --> 08:46.080
You're way too young to be
pushed out of the business.

08:46.090 --> 08:48.789
Look at all the female anchors
over 50 still going.

08:48.799 --> 08:50.247
There's Katie Couric
and Diane Sawyer

08:50.257 --> 08:53.955
and Robin Roberts
and Andrea Mitchell.

08:53.965 --> 08:56.080
You're just now
hitting your prime.

08:56.090 --> 08:59.913
Well, now I see
why they love you so much.

08:59.923 --> 09:02.664
Even I can't tell
if you're lying.

